translated: Kjellin, Axel Hjalmar, chief physician, Växjö, b. 12/3/99 in Umeå, son of Axel Olof K. and Emilia Katarina Biadin. M. 25 with Blenda Linnea Lindgren. Children: Gunilla b. 26, Ingrid Margareta b. 30, Nils Axel Jonas b. 37, Helena Kristina b. 40. — Studied in Umeå, graduating in 1918, obtained a Bachelor of Medicine degree in 1923, and a Medical Doctorate degree in Uppsala in 1928. Worked as a resident physician at Östersunds hospital in 1927, and from 1928–1929 as an acting medical officer of the second class at Växjö hospital. Became an assistant physician at the medical clinic in Uppsala in 1931, second physician at S:t Sigfrid's hospital from 1931–1932, acting first physician and second physician at S:ta Gertrud's hospital from 1932–1934, including a temporary promotion to chief physician of the third class for ten months. Became the first physician at Ryhov hospital in 1934, with temporary promotion to chief physician there annually. Worked as a prison physician for incarcerated individuals in Jönköping in 1934, a physician at Vilhemisro epileptic asylum in 1937, and chief physician at S:t Sigfrid's hospital in Växjö since 1940.
